way back before wfh, people used to actually travel to work

I recently got my hands on a copy of The Information Capital by James Chesire and Oliver Uberti (which is great and you should definitely buy it) and given that I love the city and also love doing plots and stuff with open-source data I thought Id try my hand at recreating them. This is the first one of these, from page 43 of the book showing commuter flows from the 2011 census. (side note: this is one of the fields of the census that is going to be fucked by Covid-19 in the 2021 update).

Data Sourcing

Very easy- prep-prepared and released as a csv from the census then a few easily available shapefile sets

Main Plot Recreation

Pretty easy once you do a join and cast the two points to a line. Couldnt fully work out how theyve coloured and alphad the lines but think I got close

Fiddliness

Pretty fiddly place name labels and making the inset plot
